    },
    {
      "type": "context",
      "id": "Rt8c4",
      "x": -819,
      "y": -1970,
      "name": "Naming Convention",
      "width": 616,
      "height": 1287,
      "content": "Frame Naming Convention\n\nThis document uses a structured naming convention for screen frames.\nAll agents working on this file MUST follow these rules.\n\n--- Format ---\n\nScreen/{route}#{tab}[{state}]\nScreen/{route}+{dialog}\n\n--- Rules ---\n\n1. Route path: Screen/{path}\n   Maps to the URL route of the page.\n   e.g. Screen/Projects, Screen/Settings/Tools\n\n2. Child route: Screen/{parent}/{child}\n   Nested page under a parent route.\n   e.g. Screen/Projects/New, Screen/Settings/Agent/ClaudeCode\n\n3. Tab: #{tabName}\n   Different tab within the same page.\n   e.g. #Description, #Changes\n\n4. State: [{stateName}]\n   Visual variant showing different data states of the same page.\n   e.g. [Todo], [InProgress], [Done]\n\n5. Dialog: +{dialogName}\n   Modal dialog overlaid on the parent page.\n   e.g. +Conflict, +AddTool, +Start\n\n--- Examples ---\n\nScreen/Projects              - Project list page\nScreen/Projects/New           - New project form\nScreen/Project                - Kanban board for a project\nScreen/Project/Task#Description[InProgress]\n  - Task detail, Description tab, InProgress state\nScreen/Project/Task#Changes[InProgress]\n  - Task detail, Changes tab, InProgress state\nScreen/Project/Task+Conflict  - Conflict dialog on task page\nScreen/Settings/Tools+AddTool - Add tool dialog on Tools page\nScreen/Settings/Agent+Start   - Start agent dialog\n\n--- Layout Groups ---\n\nScreens are arranged in a 2D grid using both columns and rows.\n\nColumns (by route prefix):\n  Col 1 (x=700):  Projects (Screen/Projects*)\n  Col 2 (x=2180): Project  (Screen/Project*) - #Description\n  Col 3 (x=3680): Project  (Screen/Project*) - #Changes / related\n  Col 4 (x=5180): Project  (Screen/Project*) - extra variants\n  Col 5 (x=6820): Settings (Screen/Settings*)\n\nRows (by logical group, top to bottom):\n  Row A: Root screens (Kanban, ~TaskDetail)\n  Row B: [Todo] state\n  Row C: [InProgress] state + Changes\n  Row D: [InProgress] dialog overlays\n  Row E: [InReview] state + Changes\n  Row F: [Done] state\n  Row G: [Cancelled] state\n  Row H: Task dialogs\n  Row I: Project D&D dialogs (2x2 grid)\n\nEach column has a GroupLabel text node above it.\nEach cell has a SubLabel text node for identification."
    },
    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "JHFHb",
      "x": 2180,
      "y": 3980,
      "name": "Screen/Project/Task#Description[InReview]",
      "context": "InReview状態のタスク詳細フルスクリーン表示（Descriptionタブ）。エージェントの作業は一旦完了し、ユーザーがChangesタブで差分を確認する段階。チャットステータスは「Completed」でStopボタンは非表示だが、チャット入力欄は有効。次のメッセージを送信すると、タスクのステータスはIn Progressに戻り、エージェントは前回の続きから処理を再開する。Mergeはfast-forward可能な場合のみ有効。fast-forward不可の場合はMergeボタンがdisabled（opacity 0.4）になり、tooltipで理由を表示する。先にRebaseを実行する必要がある。Rebase時にコンフリクトが発生するとConflictダイアログが表示される。",
      "theme": {
        "mode": "light"
      },
      "width": 1440,
      "height": 900,
      "fill": "$bg-primary",
      "layout": "vertical",
